title: Apse
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

A semicircular or polygonal recess at the end of a church, usually behind the altar. It often has a domed or [[Vaulted|Vault]] ceiling and serves as a focal point for worship, sometimes decorated with [[Mosaic]]s or [[frescoes|Fresco]].

''Example:'' The apse [[Mosaic]] in the Church of San Vitale in Ravenna, [[Italy]].